TY  - JOUR
AU  - Tarashev, Nikola
AU  - Tsatsaronis, Kostas
AU  - Borio, Claudio
T1  -  Risk Attribution Using the Shapley Value: Methodology and Policy Applications *
PY  - 2016
Y1  - 2016/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfv028
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 20
IS  - 3
SP  - 1189
EP  - 1213
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We present the Shapley Value as a methodology for risk attribution and use it to derive measures of banks’ systemic importance. The methodology possesses attractive properties, such as fairness and efficiency. It also leads naturally to a framework for the analysis of different drivers of systemic importance: bank size, bank-specific risk, and the commonality of banks’ exposures. We prove that, all else equal, an increase in bank size leads to a more than proportional increase in systemic importance. We also show how alternative applications of the Shapley Value methodology can be used in designing policy tools with system-wide objectives.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfv028
ER  - 



